<item>
            <title>[LU-18390] Collect memory leak debug log in /tmp/debug correctly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18390</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In recent memory leak issues, I found the following messages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;LustreError: 277252:0:(class_obd.c:900:obdclass_exit()) obd_memory max: 6549393, leaked: 20
mv: cannot stat &apos;/tmp/debug&apos;: No such file or directory
Memory leaks detected
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The debug log /tmp/debug doesn&apos;t exist because $DEBUG_RMMOD in script lustre_rmmod is not used properly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will push a patch to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
